rComments: Worst class I have taken to date. Long and monotonous. So much book work and listening to her just read what''s already there feels like a waste of time. She is nice but I need more than nice. Math classes are known for being lame so maybe make it a little fun or maybe interesting

Valerie is a such a nice teacher! She is very helpful and understanding with students. I learned a lot because of her. The class is a lot of bookwork and sections are mandatory. There are also quizzes about every week. Homework is not turn in but is based on the quizzes. I would definitely recommend her.

She's nice but there's more to teaching than being nice. All she does is read off the slides. Complete waste of time. I had to waste more of my time by getting extra help for this class. I wouldn't recommend her

One of the most boring and unhelpful teachers I have ever had. Although, yes, she's very nice, nice doesn't cut it. Avoid taking this class with her! You teach yourself the entire class because you don't learn anything in her lectures; all she does is read off the slides. Stats is just as boring of a subject as she is.

She's a newer teacher, but she did a fine job. She seems nice and is really chill with attendance/talking/sleeping, things that other professors are really uptight about. Her lecturing style could use work but as long as you do the homework its fine. Be careful it is easy to fall behind in her class toward the end.

Valerie is super nice. Don't be afraid to ask her a question. She wants to make sure everyone understands everything. We had 6 quizzes for the quarter but she drops 2. You dont have to turn in hw but it is based off the quizzes. One midterm. She curves at the end if needed. She does examples in class which are helpful and sections are helpful too.

She is really friendly and approachable but sucks at teaching. I did not learn anything from her lectures, she just reads of the slides. I had to go to MSI in order to understand the concepts. The quizzes were fairly easy if you do the homework and you understand the basic concepts.

Valerie is super friendly and approachable. Her lectures are always clear. Although she reads off the slides, she makes sure her students understand the material before moving on. If you have a question, just ask! Valerie is super cool!! :)
